								"paragraphOrdinal": 1,
								"paragraphTitle": "GOODNIGHT STORIES FOR REBEL GIRLS",
								"paragraphSubtitles": [
									"What were your favorite stories when you were young?",
									"Who were your heroes? How many were girls?"
								],
								"paragraphContents": [
									"In 2011, the University of Florida studied the number of male and female characters in children’s storybooks. There were male characters in every book. But 25 percent had no female characters. And in 37 percent of the books, the female characters didn’t talk."												
								]
							},	
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 2,
								"paragraphTitle": null,
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [
									"Two Italian women, Elena Favilli and Francesca Cavallo, decided to change this. They wanted to make a book of stories about real women. They asked people for money online to make the book. They received over a million dollars! Here are some of the women in their book:"
								]
							},
							{
								"paragraphOrdinal": 3,
								"paragraphTitle": "Maria Sibylla Merian (1647–1717)",
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [
									"Merian was a scientist. She was born in Frankfurt in Germany. When she was a child, she collected butterflies and insects. She discovered many new things about them. She traveled to South America and painted beautiful pictures of nature."
								]
							},
                            {
								"paragraphOrdinal": 4,
								"paragraphTitle": "Ada Lovelace (1815–1852)",
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [
									"Lovelace was an English mathematician. She didn’t study at public school or college. She studied at home with a teacher. When she was 12, she designed a flying machine. Also, she was the first computer programmer in the world."
								]
							},
                            {
								"paragraphOrdinal": 5,
								"paragraphTitle": "Wangari Maathai (1940–2011)",
								"paragraphSubtitles": null,
								"paragraphContents": [
									"Maathai was a Kenyan politician. She studied at universities in the US and in Germany. She wanted to help people in Kenya, so she and a group of women started to plant trees. They planted hundreds of trees and the trees helped people and nature. She received the Nobel Peace Prize in 2004."
								]
							}
